	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002242_0001"/><!--pb/@n='23r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right">28<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">th</hi></hi> March 1865 </p>
<lb/><p><hi rend="underline">Private</hi></p>
<lb/><p>The cartilage that has 
<lb/>been locking the joint 
<lb/>came out this morning 
<lb/>and <persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> &amp; M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi> Webb</persName>
<lb/>go off to <placeName>London</placeName> for 
<lb/>advice to <persName>Fergusson</persName>
<lb/>&amp; perhaps <persName>Paget</persName>. 
<lb/>We put a ring round 
<lb/>the cartilage &amp; a pad 
<lb/>over the spot from 
<lb/>which it appeared 
<lb/>to have come out. 
<lb/><choice><reg>A</reg><orig>a</orig></choice>nd they are off. 
<lb/>I promised <add place="above"><persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">rs</hi></hi> W</persName></add> to write 
<lb/>a private note to 
<lb/>you and she will 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002242_0002"/><!--pb/@n='23v'-->
<lb/>let you know when 
<lb/>they are settled - as she 
<lb/>would have much 
<lb/>more confidence 
<lb/>in the opinion of a 
<lb/>friend than of others. 
<lb/>You will please object 
<lb/>quite strongly against 
<lb/>any operation till 
<lb/>the path of the thing 
<lb/>out of the joint is 
<lb/>obliterated. You will 
<lb/>thereby do a kindness 
<lb/>to <persName>M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">rs</hi></hi> W</persName>. I said keep 
<lb/>the thing where it is &amp; 
<lb/>press it down till in 
<lb/>its own sack &amp; then 
<lb/>operate - and I hinted 
<lb/>that he had better ask the 
<lb/>surgeons to guarantee 
<lb/>him a supple &amp; not a stiff 
<lb/>joint if they operate now<reg>.</reg><addSpan spanTo="#p23r-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left margin of fol. 23r'--></addSpan>They will be at <placeName>51 Upper Brook St.</placeName> but 
<lb/>I gave her your address. <anchor xml:id="p23r-01"/></p>
			
